metadata.name: Ripples #97
metadata.description:
Ripples - Made by Zoltan Szalay @insgraphizm with P5.js
April 2022, Hungary

Features
--------
7 color themes
Light or Dark background
Number of rings
Detail of noise

Keyboard control
----------------
[f] toggle fullscreen and hide cursor
[space] manually generate new composition
[a] automatically generate new composition
[s] save image

Touchscreen
-----------
Tap left edge to automatically or right edge to manually generate a new composition.

metadata.name: Minima Monochromy X-Tex #27
metadata.description:
A simple 3D figure study. Modeled & textured & rendered in Blender.

+

6 backgrounds:

Glitch (sort of)
Grey
Noir
Rain (a slow kind of rain, cartoonish I’d say)
White
WhiteRain (it’s a simple inversion from Rain… I know you already figured it out!)

18 figures:

Rubber
Sponge
Lace ( a bit sexy!)
Ice
Fuzz
Wood
Alu
Salad (my favorite!)
Pico
Creature (scary one… really)
Crack
Forge (I had no idea how to name this none… sorry!)
Galvanized
Chain
Marble
Damask
Paper (the most poetic!)
Mold (a sad one… it happens)
+

-Created using PureSpider's layer-generating code.

metadata.name: Theatergoers #209
metadata.description:
Simple black and white blobs align to create delicate stories of an audience at their local theater. Follow their eyes in each piece to get started, but don't stare for too long——that's rude.

- press 's' to save the image at its current resolution
- press 'h' to say hello

20% of primary sales will be donated to https://www.cityarts.org/ and minters will receive a small royalty for all secondary sales.

metadata.name: Other ways #172
metadata.description:
Inspired by Paul Klee’s painting « Highways and byways », « Other ways » propose to build your own and unique generative painting.

7 features, including 4 main styles, 8 color palettes, 5 different parameters of the generative process.


Please note that the preview image is more saturated than the real token due to fxhash GPU management.

In Open Live window, press « s » to save the current image.
To get a High Resolution Image : press « r » to change the resolution for high definition, the image will reload and you can then use « s » to save the image (you can change DP in the URL to  a greater value for an even larger resolution in case you want to print it big).
This project is dimensionless, the Preview and OpenLive images are the same.

This artwork was created using p5js and scribble.

TidallyDisruptedStar. Paris. Jan 2022.

twitter : @TidallyD

metadata.name: Action Fields #263
metadata.description:
A generative painting based on abstract expressionism and the action paintings of Jackson Pollock.

Several different flow fields are used to create paths which are then painted in one of four different styles (pastel, paint, Pollock, black+gold). Additional features affect the background, path length + angles, level of detail, and mess (drips and splats). 

NOTES: 
- Some variations of the Pollock style may appear slightly different between browsers, but will render consistently in the same browser. 
- On slower devices, it may take some time to being drawing due to the background rendering.
- If you get a browser warning that the page is taking a long time, press continue.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 1200x928px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a variation of your edition at a resolution from 300 to 5,000 px. The ideal higher resolution is 2,000px.
